Package BinTree

Class Summary
BinaryTree BinaryTree defines the data type of binary trees: (i) a leaf, or (ii) a node that holds a value, a left subtree, and a right subtree.
Leaf Leaf models a tree leaf---an empty tree
Node Node models a nonempty tree node, holding a value and two subtrees
TreeCalculator TreeCalculator holds some basic methods for computing on BinaryTrees
